.TH "IDBINDEX.GETALL" "3JS" "October 21, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
IDBIndex.getAll \- IDBIndex: getAll() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]getAll()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]IDBIndex\f[R]
interface retrieves all objects that are inside the index.
.PP
There is a performance cost associated with looking at the
\f[CR]value\f[R] property of a cursor, because the object is created
lazily.
To use a feature like \f[CR]getAll()\f[R], the browser has to create all
the objects at once.
If you are just interested in looking at each of the keys, for instance,
it is more efficient to use a cursor.
If you are trying to get an array of all the objects in an object store,
though, you should use \f[CR]getAll()\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getAll()
getAll(query)
getAll(query, count)
getAll(options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
The \f[CR]getAll()\f[R] method can take separate parameters or a single
options object containing the parameters as properties.
.PP
The parameters can include:
.TP
\f[B]query\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A key or an \f[CR]IDBKeyRange\f[R] identifying the records to retrieve.
If this value is \f[CR]null\f[R] or not specified, the browser will use
an unbound key range.
.TP
\f[B]count\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The number of records to return.
If this value exceeds the number of records in the query, the browser
will only retrieve the queried records.
If it is lower than \f[CR]0\f[R] or greater than \f[CR]2\(ha32 \- 1\f[R]
a \f[CR]TypeError\f[R] exception will be thrown.
.PP
If an object parameter is specified, its properties can include:
.TP
\f[B]query\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
See the earlier \f[CR]query\f[R] definition.
.TP
\f[B]count\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
See the earlier \f[CR]count\f[R] definition.
.TP
\f[B]direction\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the direction in which the objects are
traversed.
Possible values are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]next\f[R]
The objects are traversed from the beginning, in increasing key order.
This is the default value.
.TP
\f[B]nextunique\f[R]
The objects are traversed from the beginning, in increasing key order.
For every key with duplicate objects, only the object closest to the
start is yielded.
.TP
\f[B]prev\f[R]
The objects are traversed from the end, in decreasing key order.
.TP
\f[B]prevunique\f[R]
The objects are traversed from the end, in decreasing key order.
For every key with duplicate objects, only the object closest to the
start is yielded.
.RE
.SS Return value
An \f[CR]IDBRequest\f[R] object on which subsequent events related to
this operation are fired.
.PP
If the operation is successful, the value of the request\(cqs
\f[CR]result\f[R] property is an \f[CR]Array\f[R] of the values of all
records matching the given query, up to the value of \f[CR]count\f[R],
if \f[CR]count\f[R] was supplied.
.SS Exceptions
This method may raise a \f[CR]DOMException\f[R] of the following types:
.TP
\f[B]TransactionInactiveError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if this \f[CR]IDBIndex\f[R]\(cqs transaction is inactive.
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]IDBIndex\f[R] has been deleted or removed.
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]count\f[R] parameter is not between \f[CR]0\f[R] and
\f[CR]2\(ha32 \- 1\f[R], inclusive.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myIndex = objectStore.index(\(dqindex\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] getAllRequest = myIndex.getAll();
getAllRequest.onsuccess = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(getAllRequest.result);
};
.EE
